<title type="html"><![CDATA[Tabulated data of 6502 opcodes, byte length and cycles ?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6159&amp;p=58724#p58724"><![CDATA[
<a href="http://www.gitorious.org/nesicide/nesicide2-master/blobs/master/emulator/cnes6502.cpp" class="postlink">Here</a>.  The table starts on line 139.  I believe it is correct and contains all undocumented and illegal opcodes.<br /><br />I didn't find much use in organizing it by opcode/addressing mode.  My assembler could perhaps be a bit faster once it finds an opcode if it only had to search through the addressing modes in another dimension from the opcode index.  But I like the 1-d approach.<br /><br />Undocumented opcodes may not be named exactly as you would expect...there's quite a few different opinions on the appropriate names for these opcodes.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3705">cpow</a> — Sun Mar 21, 2010 10:48 am</p><hr />
